<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="336" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,703,1035,1098]" box="[151,325,1071,1098]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,247,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,196,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-24@38.[151,1436,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 20. Lamtoana exigua. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. pygofer dorsal appendage; d. pygofer ventral appendage; e. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; f. subgenital plate, dorsal view; g. style, dorsal view; h. connective; i. aedeagus, lateral view; j. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413909/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[258,286,1071,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">27</figureCitation>
i–l)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1143,1818]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1143,1169]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Description.</emphasis>
Body off white, heavily marked with dark brown (specimen preserved in ethanol before examination). Vertex with large brown patch apically at transition from vertex to face, with pair of brown patches medially, near to each other; tip of anteclypeus darkened. Pronotum with middle anterior margin and central part brown. Basal triangles of mesonotum dark. Forewing with inner margin of clavus darkened. (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1126,1251,1278]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 27</figureCitation>
i–l)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1143,1818]" box="[199,1037,1287,1314]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
Male abdominal apodemes 2S (
<figureCitation box="[553,647,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 27a</figureCitation>
) extended to middle of sternite IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1143,1818]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
Pygofer dorsal appendage (
<figureCitation box="[504,629,1323,1350]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 27b, c</figureCitation>
) with apical part short, apex blunt; ventral appendage (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1371,1323,1350]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 27b, d</figureCitation>
) very short, germ-like. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[546,673,1359,1386]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 27b, f</figureCitation>
) with about 4 macrosetae. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1153,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1110,1153,1359,1385]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.7" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" unit="g" value="27.0">27g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) with pointed, tooth-like process extended form subapical inner edge of apical part, upper part of preapical lobe weakly sclerotized and serrated. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[367,465,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 27h</figureCitation>
) with manubrium wide and long, lateral arms thick and short. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1309,1428,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,191,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-20@47.[147,1440,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 27. a–d. Lamtoana flavoscuta; e–h. Lamtoana nakulabica; i–l. Lamtoana exigua; m–p. Nsesa cameroonica; q–t. Nsimbala kinlaza; u–x. Nsimbala wenea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413923/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs 27i, j</figureCitation>
) with apical processes moderately long, extended away from shaft in caudal view; dorsal apodeme well developed, widened in caudal view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1143,1818]" box="[199,619,1539,1566]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,1539,1565]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Measurement.</emphasis>
Male length 
<quantity box="[519,615,1539,1566]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.50mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
